  <head>
    {%- comment -%} ═══ GEO-LANGUAGE AUTO-REDIRECT — must be FIRST in <head> ═══ {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- unless request.design_mode -%}
      {%- assign _geo_country = localization.country.iso_code -%}
      {%- assign _cur_locale = request.locale.iso_code | downcase -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        Geo → language map (IP-based, from Shopify Markets):
        DE/AT/CH/LI/LU  → de   (German-speaking)
        PL              → pl   (Polish)
        SE              → sv   (Swedish)
        anywhere else   → en   (default fallback, incl. English-speaking
                                countries US/GB/IE/AU/NZ/CA + any country
                                we don't have a localised version for yet)
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign _expected = 'en' -%}
      {%- if _geo_country == 'DE' or _geo_country == 'AT' or _geo_country == 'CH' or _geo_country == 'LI' or _geo_country == 'LU' -%}
        {%- assign _expected = 'de' -%}
      {%- elsif _geo_country == 'PL' -%}
        {%- assign _expected = 'pl' -%}
      {%- elsif _geo_country == 'SE' -%}
        {%- assign _expected = 'sv' -%}
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        Does the current URL already carry an explicit locale prefix
        (e.g. /pt/, /nl/, /da/, /sv/)? If so, the visitor — OR Googlebot / the
        Google Shopping feed crawler — explicitly requested that locale, so we
        must NOT auto-redirect away from it.

        WHY (Merchant Center fix): the old code redirected EVERY localized
        landing page whose geo-expected locale differed (e.g. /pt/products/x →
        /en/products/x). Google Merchant crawls the exact feed URL, saw it
        redirect, and flagged ~all non-DE products as "Product page
        unavailable" (179 disapprovals). It also bounced legitimate localized
        traffic out of its own market. We now ONLY auto-localize from the
        default (no-prefix) URLs; explicit locale URLs are served as-is.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign _req_seg = request.path | split: '/' -%}
      {%- assign _req_locale = _req_seg[1] | default: '' -%}
      {%- assign _known_locales = 'en,pl,sv,da,nl,fr,it,es,cs,hu,ro,sk,fi,el,pt' | split: ',' -%}
      {%- assign _on_locale_url = false -%}
      {%- if _known_locales contains _req_locale -%}
        {%- assign _on_locale_url = true -%}
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- if _expected != _cur_locale and _on_locale_url == false -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          We are on a default (no-prefix → de) URL and the visitor's geo wants a
          different language. Build the localized target. No locale-prefix
          stripping is needed here because no-prefix paths never carry one.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign _path = request.path -%}
        {%- if _path == blank -%}{%- assign _path = '/' -%}{%- endif -%}

        {%- if _expected == 'de' -%}
          {%- assign _redirect_url = _path -%}
        {%- elsif _path == '/' -%}
          {%- assign _redirect_url = '/' | append: _expected -%}
        {%- else -%}
          {%- assign _redirect_url = '/' | append: _expected | append: _path -%}
        {%- endif -%}

        <script>if(document.cookie.indexOf('karinex_lang_set')===-1){window.location.replace('{{ _redirect_url }}');}</script>
        <noscript><meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0;url={{ _redirect_url }}"></noscript>
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endunless -%}

